The paper deals with termination analysis of probabilistic programs, which involves logical reasoning and mathematical analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves probabilistic programming, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of ranking supermartingales and supermartingales suggests a connection to probability theory and stochastic processes, which are covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with termination analysis, which is related to formal verification, and hence, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category.
